HEADWORD: Eschscholtzia
<hw>Esch*scholtz"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
Named after <person>Dr. <etsep>Eschscholtz</etsep></person>, a German
botanist.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of papaveraceous plants,
found in California and upon the west coast of North America, some
species of which produce beautiful yellow, orange, rose-colored, or
white flowers; the California poppy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

